How to connect 

1)To access the AWS linux EC2 from windows – Putty need to be installed. 
https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSEC2/latest/UserGuide/putty.html
and give the below inputs to putty and then connect 
SSH/ Auth/ privatekey for authentication: Private_key.ppk (uploaded to bitbucket) 
Hostname: ec2-user@ ec2-54-160-192-161.compute-1.amazonaws.com 

2) Mysql login credentials
 Endpoint: mysql-db.cbvvxkzv412m.us-east-1.rds.amazonaws.com 
 Port : 3306 
 Database name: ItenaryPlannerdb 
 Password: database 
command to login: mysql -u admin -h mysql-db.cbvvxkzv412m.us-east-1.rds.amazonaws.com -p 

3) Commands to run Django server 
 cd pydjangoenv 
 source env/bin/activate 
 cd ItenaryPlanner 
 python manage.py runserver 0.0.0.0:8000 
 
 
 
 Installation Procedure 
 
1)Created a Amazon web service account and a virtual EC2 machine also launched 
2)Installation of Apache server and MariaDB Database in AWS EC2 machine (Not used anymore) 
https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSEC2/latest/UserGuide/AccessingInstancesLinux.html
Walkthrough: Set up an Apache web server and serve Amazon EFS files - Amazon Elastic File System
How to Install Apache Web Server on Amazon Linux 2 - CloudKatha
How To Install MariaDB 10.6 on Amazon Linux 2 | ComputingForGeeks
3) Installation of Django server and MySQL database 
 
Setting up a Django + MySQL Development Environment on AWS EC2 Linux 2 - Bing video
Python3 -m venv pydjangoenv/env - create a directory for django 
cd pydjangoenv - to change the working directory 
source env/bin/activate 
pip install django - to install django 
pip install mysqlclient – to install mysql 
 
Django-admin startproject ItenaryPlanner – a new project named ItenaryPlanner created 
Cd ItenaryPlanner – manage.py and ItenaryPlanner in this directory 
Cd ItenaryPlanner – settings.py in the ItenaryPlanner folder 
Nano settings.py - nano command is used to edit the settings.py ( databases and accessible host 
updated) 
CD.. 
Python manage.py runserver 0.0.0.0:8000 - to run the Django server 
 
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/20239232/django-server-error-port-is-already-in-use - used to 
resolve an error in tcp usage 
 
Writing your first Django app, part 1 | Django documentation | Django (djangoproject.com) - the 
procedure in this page is used to create a sample web page 
>Filename is used to create an empty file 
 
 
 
 
 
 
