b) Mate Desktop + tigervnc viewer
Installation details - https://aws.amazon.com/premiumsupport/knowledge-center/ec2-linux-2-
install-gui/
Install tigervnc64-x.y.z.exe (64-bit) or tigervnc-x.y.z.exe (32-bit), where x.y.z represents the latest 
version. https://tigervnc.org/ 
When opening the connection with PuTTY, configure port forwarding, and then open the connection:
 From the Connection menu, select SSH, and then select Tunnels.
 Enter 5901 in the Source Port field.
 Enter localhost:5901 in the Destination field.
 Select Add. 
Open SSH 
Then open tigervnc viewer, 
Username: localhost:1 
Password: matedesktop